<P>Adapt in what fashion. I have only to be attacked by mages that I con green too so far while I have been sitting or zoning from a fight that I am half dead from. I only have 440 HP at lvl 15 and all have killed me in 3 shots or less (this was before patch downsizing). There is nothing I can do to combat it at my current lvl that I am aware of short of being another caster. Its not that I fear it I just cannot effectively combat it. I know of jboots and the like but cannot attain them yet. May not be that good against NPC but has hit me every time from a character that is 5 lvls above me. I am new to the PvP side of EQ and will learn but as it stands I have had some harsh lessons. But to me playing a caster is not the answer, I mean everyone else is casters, wheres the fun in that?

<P>&gt; You need to adapt if root scares you so much you wan't it gone
<BR>&gt; you must be a terrible tank. Root is not that good thank you
<BR>&gt; very much. If you think root is bad why don't you get hit with
<BR>&gt; grasping roots or ensenaring roots. Your a tank you got like a
<BR>&gt; 1000 hp so live with root cause it's not that great of a spell.
<BR>&gt; That's why I have the spell Cancel Magic.
